    "Id": "vehiclechassisdef_CHEVALIER",
    "Name": "Chevalier",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Chevalier Light Tank (Standard)</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Standard </color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>7/12 (Wheeled)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>190 Fusion</color></b>\n\nThe Chevalier Light Tank was produced by and for the Star League, but its numbers were decimated during the Succession Wars, as the Successor States often cannibalized them for parts. Only Millennium Industries of Terra continued to produce the design, which was later acquired by ComStar. Despite its weak armament compared to modern designs, the Chevalier is extremely ammunition-efficient, allowing it to stay in the fight longer than other vehicles of the same weight class. It mounts an ER Large Laser in its turret and a pair of front-mounted Streak SRM-2s to exploit any weaknesses in an opponent's armor.",
